## Workspace Philosophy

This workspace is not limited to one agent.
All agent teams may be used here when useful.

Typical combinations:

- `{{WORKSPACE_NAME}} + CSO`
- `{{WORKSPACE_NAME}} + CFO`
- `{{WORKSPACE_NAME}} + CTO`
- `{{WORKSPACE_NAME}} + Marketer`
- `{{WORKSPACE_NAME}} + CBO`

The workspace sets the domain context.
The agent team sets the perspective.

## Index-First Loading Order

Before substantive work:

1. read this file
2. read `./_Master/`
3. read `./_Index.md`
4. only then load project-specific files

## Core Rules

- Final outputs should stay inside this workspace.
- Existing files must be edited surgically.
- Use `{YYYY}-{MM}-{DD}_{Keyword}.md` for dated outputs.
- `*_MOC.md` files are not normal working outputs (Obsidian graph navigation only).

## Critical Actions

The following require explicit user approval before execution:

`DELETE_FILE` / `OVERWRITE_EXISTING` / `SEND_EMAIL` / `DEPLOY_CODE` / `EXECUTE_SHELL` / `MOVE_FILE`

## Default Loading Paths

- `./_Master/`
- `./_Index.md`
- relevant subproject folders

## Frontmatter Guide

Adjust to your domain. Example schema:

- `Related`: pointer to a Notion / Linear / external system reference
- `Type`: project category (e.g. `Project_A`, `Initiative_X`)
- `Topic`: doc category (e.g. `Strategy`, `Report`, `Spec`)
- `tags`: free-form labels

The frontmatter validation hook (`arsenal/verify_frontmatter_block.js`) reads `arsenal/audit_exclusions.json` `frontmatter_blocking` to determine which workspaces enforce required fields. Adjust both files together.
